==English==

===Etymology===
From the Greek ''[[metera]]'' meaning mother.

===Noun===
'''metro'''  (''plural:'' '''[[metros]]''')
# An underground system not based in America or in London, particular the Paris one.
# A tube train of the above.
# Short for metropolitian (where the term for tube is derived.)

===See also===
*[[metro-]] ''prefix''

